body:
That's tricky indeed. IMO we should ensure once the "relevant event" is received we eventually sync our data before the app is closed. This would minimize the risk of data inconsistency.

To keep the network bandwidth low we should probably use some [Debounce](https://reactivex.io/documentation/operators/debounce.html) mechanism instead of performing a backup for every "relevant event". Example:
```
func handleContactRequest() {
    ...
    backup.debounce() // ensure backup is performed before app is closed, but not more often than once per specified interval
}
```
call `backup.debounce()` in every "relevant event".

Another, very naive solution, would be to keep the "dirty" state of the backup and perform backup just once before the app is closed. It has a drawback though, as it may block the app just before it is closed.
```
func handleContactRequest() {
    ...
    backup.makeDirty()
}
func beforeAppExit() {
   if (backup.isDirty()) {
       backup.perform() // blocking
   }
}
```
